This paper is primarily focused on sentiment analysis, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the use of pre-processing techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of CNNs and RNNs also suggests that it could be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of bilingual embeddings, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves the representation of language in a vector space.
